result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob S Krueger was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Statutory costs assessed.   If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

No alcohol or controlled substances except by prescription. Random UA's are authorized. Any counseling deemed appropriate by agent; specifically AODA assessment, treatment and after care. Must continue current counseling program and take all medications as prescribed. Must be under the care of a psychiatrist and said care may not be terminated except by medical advise. Must obtain and maintain full time verifiable employment or attend school full time or a combination of both equal to full time. May not enter into or loiter near any taverns, bars or liquor stores. May enter restaurants that sell alcohol but may not drink. Do not associate with any known drug dealers or users. No contact, directly or indirectly, with victim NRF. No contact with KF. Defendant must submit a DNA sample as required by law unless it has been previously provided, however, defendant must pay mandatory DNA surcharge. Firearm warning given. Voting is prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights have been restored.  Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on supervision.
